Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} for your rice. Rinse the @Brown Basmati Rice{175%g} under running water for ~{30%seconds}. Once the water is rapidly boiling add the rice and cook for around ~{25%minutes}. When the rice is 2mins from done, add in the @Fresh Peas{1/2%cup}.

Meanwhile, chop the base from the @Pak Choi{1} and discard it. Very, very thinly chop the bok choy widthways (i.e. 'shred' it). Remove the core from the @Red Pepper{1} and chop half of it into little 1/2 cm cubes and slice the rest into 1/2 cm strips. Finely chop the @Spring Onion{2} widthways, separating the white and green parts.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add your @Cashew Nuts{2}. Toast them in the pan for a few mins until they are brown then remove.

> Our usual warning: Watch them like a hawk as once they start to brown off they can burn quickly!

Chop your @Roaming Roosters Pork Fillet{1} up into tiny bite-sized pieces for later. Put your feet up for a bit - the rest of the action happens when the rice is almost done.

Once the rice is ready you can drain the peas and rice together.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a pan on high heat ready for your pork. Once it's really hot, fry off the pork with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} then remove once browned off. Add a bit more @oil{1%tbsp} and cook the sliced red pepper, the whites of the spring onions and the bok choy. Cook for a few mins until they have browned off, then add back the pork and tip in the rice.

Toss the ingredients in the pan for about ~{5%minutes} to start browning off the rice. Make some space in the pan and add the @Curry Spice{1/2%tsp} with @water{2%tbsp} and the @Sweet Chilli Marinade{2%tsp}. Once the curry powder, water and chilli marinade are mixed, toss everything together.

Now add the @Fish Sauce{1/2%tsp} bit by bit until the seasoning is just right. Stir in the greens of the spring onions, the cashew nuts and the remaining raw red.